{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So let me just start with my story."},{"time":3000,"text":"So I tore my knee joint meniscus cartilage"},{"time":5000,"text":"playing soccer in college."},{"time":8000,"text":"Then I went on to tear my ACL, the ligament in my knee,"},{"time":11000,"text":"and then developed an arthritic knee."},{"time":13000,"text":"And I'm sure that many of you in this audience have that same story,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and, by the way, I married a woman"},{"time":18000,"text":"who has exactly the same story."},{"time":21000,"text":"So this motivated me to become an orthopedic surgeon"},{"time":24000,"text":"and to see if I couldn't focus on solutions for those problems"},{"time":27000,"text":"that would keep me playing sports and not limit me."},{"time":31000,"text":"So with that, let me just show you a quick video"},{"time":34000,"text":"to get you in the mood of what we're trying to explain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"Narrator: We are all aware of the risk of cancer,"},{"time":39000,"text":"but there's another disease"},{"time":41000,"text":"that's destined to affect even more of us: arthritis."},{"time":44000,"text":"Cancer may kill you, but when you look at the numbers,"},{"time":46000,"text":"arthritis ruins more lives."},{"time":48000,"text":"Assuming you live a long life, there's a 50 percent chance"},{"time":50000,"text":"you'll develop arthritis."},{"time":53000,"text":"And it's not just aging that causes arthritis."},{"time":55000,"text":"Common injuries can lead to decades of pain,"},{"time":58000,"text":"until our joints quite literally grind to a halt."},{"time":61000,"text":"Desperate for a solution, we've turned to engineering"},{"time":63000,"text":"to design artificial components"},{"time":65000,"text":"to replace our worn-out body parts,"},{"time":67000,"text":"but in the midst of the modern buzz"},{"time":69000,"text":"around the promises of a bionic body,"},{"time":71000,"text":"shouldn't we stop and ask if there's a better, more natural way?"},{"time":76000,"text":"Let's consider an alternative path."},{"time":78000,"text":"What if all the replacements our bodies need"},{"time":81000,"text":"already exist in nature,"},{"time":83000,"text":"or within our own stem cells?"},{"time":85000,"text":"This is the field of biologic replacements,"},{"time":87000,"text":"where we replace worn-out parts with new, natural ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"Kevin Stone: And so, the mission is:"},{"time":92000,"text":"how do I treat these things biologically?"},{"time":94000,"text":"And let's talk about both what I did for my wife,"},{"time":96000,"text":"and what I've done for hundreds of other patients."},{"time":98000,"text":"First thing for my wife,"},{"time":100000,"text":"and the most common thing I hear from my patients,"},{"time":102000,"text":"particularly in the 40- to 80-year-old age group, 70-year-old age group,"},{"time":105000,"text":"is they come in and say,"},{"time":107000,"text":"\"Hey, Doc, isn't there just a shock absorber you can put in my knee?"},{"time":109000,"text":"I'm not ready for joint replacement.\""},{"time":111000,"text":"And so for her, I put in a human meniscus allograft donor"},{"time":114000,"text":"right into that [knee] joint space."},{"time":116000,"text":"And [the allograft] replaces [the missing meniscus]."},{"time":118000,"text":"And then for that unstable ligament,"},{"time":120000,"text":"we put in a human donor ligament"},{"time":122000,"text":"to stabilize the knee."},{"time":124000,"text":"And then for the damaged arthritis on the surface,"},{"time":127000,"text":"we did a stem cell paste graft,"},{"time":129000,"text":"which we designed in 1991,"},{"time":131000,"text":"to regrow that articular cartilage surface"},{"time":134000,"text":"and give it back a smooth surface there."},{"time":137000,"text":"So here's my wife's bad knee on the left,"},{"time":139000,"text":"and her just hiking now"},{"time":141000,"text":"four months later in Aspen, and doing well."},{"time":144000,"text":"And it works, not just for my wife, but certainly for other patients."},{"time":147000,"text":"The girl on the video, Jen Hudak,"},{"time":149000,"text":"just won the Superpipe in Aspen"},{"time":151000,"text":"just nine months after having destroyed her knee,"},{"time":154000,"text":"as you see in the other image --"},{"time":156000,"text":"and having a paste graft to that knee."},{"time":158000,"text":"And so we can regrow these surfaces biologically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162000,"text":"So with all this success,"},{"time":164000,"text":"why isn't that good enough, you might ask."},{"time":167000,"text":"Well the reason is because there's not enough donor cycles."},{"time":170000,"text":"There's not enough young, healthy people"},{"time":172000,"text":"falling off their motorcycle"},{"time":174000,"text":"and donating that tissue to us."},{"time":177000,"text":"And the tissue's very expensive."},{"time":180000,"text":"And so that's not going to be a solution"},{"time":182000,"text":"that's going to get us global with biologic tissue."},{"time":185000,"text":"But the solution is animal tissue"},{"time":187000,"text":"because it's plentiful, it's cheap,"},{"time":189000,"text":"you can get it from young, healthy tissues,"},{"time":192000,"text":"but the barrier is immunology."},{"time":194000,"text":"And the specific barrier"},{"time":196000,"text":"is a specific epitope"},{"time":198000,"text":"called the galactosyl, or gal epitope."},{"time":200000,"text":"So if we're going to transplant animal tissues to people,"},{"time":202000,"text":"we have to figure out a way to get rid of that epitope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"So my story in working with animal tissues"},{"time":207000,"text":"starts in 1984."},{"time":209000,"text":"And I started first"},{"time":211000,"text":"with cow Achilles tendon,"},{"time":213000,"text":"where we would take the cow Achilles tendon,"},{"time":215000,"text":"which is type-I collagen,"},{"time":217000,"text":"strip it of its antigens"},{"time":219000,"text":"by degrading it with an acid and detergent wash"},{"time":222000,"text":"and forming it into a regeneration template."},{"time":225000,"text":"We would then take that regeneration template"},{"time":227000,"text":"and insert it into the missing meniscus cartilage"},{"time":230000,"text":"to regrow that in a patient's knee."},{"time":233000,"text":"We've now done that procedure,"},{"time":235000,"text":"and it's been done worldwide in over 4,000 cases,"},{"time":237000,"text":"so it's an FDA-approved and worldwide-accepted way"},{"time":240000,"text":"to regrow the meniscus."},{"time":242000,"text":"And that's great when I can degrade the tissue."},{"time":245000,"text":"But what happens for your ligament when I need an intact ligament?"},{"time":248000,"text":"I can't grind it up in a blender."},{"time":250000,"text":"So in that case,"},{"time":252000,"text":"I have to design -- and we designed with Uri Galili and Tom Turek --"},{"time":255000,"text":"an enzyme wash"},{"time":257000,"text":"to wash away, or strip,"},{"time":259000,"text":"those galactosyl epitopes"},{"time":261000,"text":"with a specific enzyme."},{"time":263000,"text":"And we call that a \"gal stripping\" technique."},{"time":266000,"text":"What we do is humanize the tissue."},{"time":268000,"text":"It's by gal stripping that tissue"},{"time":270000,"text":"we humanize it (Laughter),"},{"time":272000,"text":"and then we can put it back"},{"time":274000,"text":"into a patient's knee."},{"time":278000,"text":"And we've done that. Now we've taken pig ligament --"},{"time":280000,"text":"young, healthy, big tissue,"},{"time":282000,"text":"put it into 10 patients in an FDA-approved trial --"},{"time":285000,"text":"and then one of our patients went on to have"},{"time":287000,"text":"three Canadian Masters Downhill championships --"},{"time":290000,"text":"on his \"pig-lig,\" as he calls it. So we know it can work."},{"time":292000,"text":"And there's a wide clinical trial of this tissue now pending."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"So what about the next step?"},{"time":299000,"text":"What about getting to a total biologic knee replacement,"},{"time":301000,"text":"not just the parts?"},{"time":303000,"text":"How are we going to revolutionize artificial joint replacement?"},{"time":306000,"text":"Well here's how we're going to do it."},{"time":308000,"text":"So what we're going to do is take"},{"time":310000,"text":"an articular cartilage"},{"time":312000,"text":"from a young, healthy pig,"},{"time":314000,"text":"strip it of its antigens,"},{"time":316000,"text":"load it with your stem cells,"},{"time":319000,"text":"then put it back on to that"},{"time":321000,"text":"arthritic surface in your knee,"},{"time":324000,"text":"tack it on there, have you heal that surface"},{"time":327000,"text":"and then create a new biologic surface for your knee."},{"time":333000,"text":"So that's our biologic approach right now."},{"time":337000,"text":"We're going to rebuild your knee with the parts."},{"time":339000,"text":"We're going to resurface it with a completely new surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"But we have other advantages from the animal kingdom."},{"time":345000,"text":"There's a benefit of 400 million years"},{"time":347000,"text":"of ambulation."},{"time":349000,"text":"We can harness those benefits."},{"time":351000,"text":"We can use thicker, younger, better tissues"},{"time":354000,"text":"than you might have injured in your knee,"},{"time":356000,"text":"or that you might have when you're 40, 50 or 60."},{"time":358000,"text":"We can do it as an outpatient procedure."},{"time":360000,"text":"We can strip that tissue very economically,"},{"time":363000,"text":"and so this is how we can get biologic knee replacement"},{"time":366000,"text":"to go global."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"And so welcome to super biologics."},{"time":370000,"text":"It's not hardware."},{"time":372000,"text":"It's not software."},{"time":375000,"text":"It's bioware."},{"time":377000,"text":"It's version 2.0 of you."},{"time":380000,"text":"And so with that, coming to a --"},{"time":382000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":384000,"text":"coming to an operating theater near you soon, I believe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}